Class Project

java.lang.Object
Project
public class Project
extends java.lang.Object
Class to create Project objects. Project objects are managed by Poise class.
Author:
Lindsey
See Also:
ProjectContact, Poise

    • Project

      public Project​(int projectNum, java.lang.String projectName, java.lang.String buildType, int ERFNum, java.lang.String address, double totalFee, double totalPaid, java.util.Date deadline, ProjectContact customer, ProjectContact contractor, ProjectContact architect, java.lang.String projectManager, java.lang.String completionDate)
      Project object constructor
      Parameters:
      projectNum - - Unique identifying number for the project.
      projectName - - Project Name.
      buildType - - The type of building for the project (House, apartment, hut, etc.).
      ERFNum - - The ERF number at the build site.
      address - - The address for the build site.
      totalFee - - The total fee for the project, in rands.
      totalPaid - - The total amount paid by the customer, in rands.
      deadline - - The project deadline.
      customer - - The customer-type project contact object.
      contractor - - The contractor-type project contact object.
      architect - - The architect-type project contact object.
      projectManager - - The project manager for project.
      completionDate - - The date at which the project was completed.
